---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Insurance for International Pilots | Compare Expat Plans";
const description = "Health insurance guide for Pilots working internationally, covering aviation positions abroad, airline careers, and global pilot opportunities.";
const headline = "Insurance for International Pilots";
const subheadline = "Coverage solutions for Pilots working abroad, flying internationally, and pursuing careers across airlines and aviation operations worldwide.";
const canonicalPath = "/guides/pilot-insurance";
const heroBackgroundImage = "/images/guides/pilot-insurance-hero.png";

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'coverage-needs', label: 'Coverage Needs' },
  { id: 'work-settings', label: 'Work Settings' },
  { id: 'credentials', label: 'Credentials' },
  { id: 'occupational-health', label: 'Occupational Health' },
  { id: 'work-demands', label: 'Work Demands' },
  { id: 'career-considerations', label: 'Career Considerations' },
  { id: 'faqs', label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  heroBackgroundImage={heroBackgroundImage}
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>International Pilot Careers</h2>
      <p>
        Pilots operate aircraft safely, navigating routes and managing flights. International pilot careers offer opportunities to fly for global airlines, work with diverse crews, and experience aviation across different regulatory environments.
      </p>
      <p>
        International pilot opportunities exist through major international airlines, regional carriers, cargo operators, and corporate aviation operations worldwide.
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide addresses insurance considerations for Pilots working abroad across airlines and aviation operations worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="coverage-needs">
      <h2>Coverage Needs for Pilots</h2>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={[
          { key: 'need', header: 'Coverage Need' },
          { key: 'why', header: 'Why It Matters' },
          { key: 'typical', header: 'Coverage Situation?' },
        ]}
        rows={[
          { need: 'General health coverage', why: 'Medical certificate requirements', typical: 'Usually employer-provided' },
          { need: 'Loss of license', why: 'Career-ending medical conditions', typical: 'Critical for pilots' },
          { need: 'Aviation medical', why: 'Medical certification support', typical: 'Essential for role' },
          { need: 'Mental health support', why: 'Stress and fatigue management', typical: 'Important for role' },
          { need: 'Wellness support', why: 'Circadian disruption', typical: 'Often included' },
          { need: 'Hearing coverage', why: 'Cockpit noise exposure', typical: 'Consider including' },
        ]}
      />

      <h3>Medical Certificate Requirements</h3>
      <p>
        Pilots require valid medical certificates to fly. Losing medical certification means losing the ability to work. Health conditions that might be minor inconveniences for others can be career-ending for pilots. Loss of license insurance is essential protection against medical decertification.
      </p>
      <p>
        Maintaining health proactively is career-critical for pilots.
      </p>

      <h3>Circadian Disruption</h3>
      <p>
        Long-haul pilots cross multiple time zones regularly, causing significant circadian disruption. Night flying, irregular schedules, and jet lag create ongoing health challenges. Wellness support and fatigue management are important for sustainable aviation careers.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-settings">
      <h2>Coverage by Work Setting</h2>

      <h3>Major Airline</h3>
      <p>
        International flag carrier. Comprehensive benefits. Union contracts often. Major airlines offer stability.
      </p>

      <h3>Low-Cost Carrier</h3>
      <p>
        International LCC. Airline benefits. High utilization. LCCs offer opportunity.
      </p>

      <h3>Cargo Operator</h3>
      <p>
        Freight airline. Cargo carrier benefits. Night operations common. Cargo offers compensation.
      </p>

      <h3>Corporate Aviation</h3>
      <p>
        Business jet operator. Employer benefits. Schedule flexibility. Corporate offers variety.
      </p>

      <h3>Charter</h3>
      <p>
        Charter operator. Operator benefits vary. On-demand flying. Charter offers flexibility.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Coverage for Pilots"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Pilots working abroad across airlines and aviation operations worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Pilot Plans"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

    <section id="credentials">
      <h2>Credentials and Professional Recognition</h2>

      <h3>Pilot License</h3>
      <p>
        ATPL or equivalent. Type ratings. Regulatory license. License required to fly.
      </p>

      <h3>Medical Certificate</h3>
      <p>
        First-class aviation medical. Regular renewal. Health requirements. Medical essential.
      </p>

      <h3>Flight Hours</h3>
      <p>
        Logged flight time. Aircraft experience. Route qualification. Hours build capability.
      </p>

      <h3>Type Ratings</h3>
      <p>
        Aircraft-specific certification. Simulator training. Currency requirements. Ratings enable positions.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="occupational-health">
      <h2>Occupational Health Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Medical Fitness</h3>
      <p>
        Certification requirements. Regular examinations. Health standards. Medical coverage critical.
      </p>

      <h3>Circadian Disruption</h3>
      <p>
        Time zone crossing. Irregular schedules. Sleep challenges. Wellness support important.
      </p>

      <h3>Radiation Exposure</h3>
      <p>
        High-altitude cosmic radiation. Long-haul exposure. Cumulative effects. Monitoring valuable.
      </p>

      <h3>Hearing</h3>
      <p>
        Cockpit noise. Headset use. Long-term exposure. Hearing coverage helpful.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-demands">
      <h2>Managing Work Demands</h2>

      <h3>Operations</h3>
      <p>
        Flight planning. Route management. Weather assessment. Operations ensure safety.
      </p>

      <h3>Safety</h3>
      <p>
        Procedures compliance. Emergency preparedness. Decision-making. Safety is paramount.
      </p>

      <h3>Crew Coordination</h3>
      <p>
        Cockpit resource management. Crew communication. Team effectiveness. Coordination enables operations.
      </p>

      <h3>Regulatory</h3>
      <p>
        Compliance requirements. Currency maintenance. Documentation. Regulatory adherence required.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="career-considerations">
      <h2>Career Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Strong Demand</h3>
      <p>
        Pilot shortage global. Aviation growth continuing. Experienced pilots valued. Demand strong.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Paths</h3>
      <p>
        Captain. Training Captain. Check Pilot. Management. Multiple paths available.
      </p>

      <h3>Credential Portability</h3>
      <p>
        ATPL recognized globally. License conversion needed. Type ratings transfer. Core skills portable.
      </p>

      <h3>Field Evolution</h3>
      <p>
        Technology advancement. Automation integration. Sustainability focus. Field evolving continuously.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="faqs">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">I'm a pilot considering international work. What should I know?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Airlines provide comprehensive benefits. License conversion required. Medical fitness critical. Loss of license coverage essential.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do employers provide international coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Airlines typically yes. Benefits often comprehensive. Loss of license may be separate. Verify coverage carefully.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is loss of license insurance important?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Critical for pilots. Medical conditions career-ending. Financial protection essential. Priority coverage.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do pilot credentials transfer internationally?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Flying skills universal. License conversion needed. Type ratings transfer often. Core competence portable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is circadian disruption a significant concern?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes for long-haul pilots. Sleep quality affected. Health implications. Wellness support valuable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What's the career outlook?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Global pilot shortage. Strong demand. Good compensation. Outlook excellent.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start by evaluating airline benefits packages. Prioritize loss of license insurance for career protection. Ensure comprehensive aviation medical support. Consider wellness support for circadian challenges.
      </p>
      <p>
        Pilots connect the world. Your coverage should support aviation careers—addressing medical and certification demands, covering health maintenance, and protecting you across flying worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Protect Your Aviation Career"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Pilots working abroad across airlines and aviation operations worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

  </article>
</PageShell>
